Return a JSON object with these fields:
- entity_updates: list of {id, patch: {status?, last_referenced_update?, data?}}
- new_relationships: list of {source_id, target_id, rel_type, data?}
- removed_relationships: list of {source_id, target_id, rel_type}
- timeline_events: list of {description, involved_entities: [string]}
- foreshadowing_updates: list of {id, new_status, add_reference?}
- theme_stance_updates: list of {id, new_stance}. ONLY emit when the prose
  *materially* shifts how a listed theme is being treated (e.g. moving from
  "exploring" to "questioning" a proposition, or from "questioning" to
  "subverting"). Do NOT emit for every chapter — most updates should have
  an empty list here. Valid stances: exploring, affirming, questioning,
  subverting.
- motive_resolutions: list of {character_id, motive_id, resolved_at_update}.
  ONLY emit when the prose shows the character confronting, naming, or
  decisively moving past the listed unconscious motive. This is a rare
  event. Set resolved_at_update to the current update number. Do NOT emit
  speculative resolutions — default is an empty list.
